erience</td><td>20,000</td><td>60</td><td>6</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>ESP</td><td>Gives telepathy (the ability to detect all sentient creatures), and a bonus of +5+MB(5) to searching</td><td>25,000</td><td>60</td><td>8</td><td>(2)</td></tr><tr><td>Devotion</td><td>Sustains and gives a bonus of +1+MB(3) to wisdom and charisma; gives resistance to fire, light and darkness; protects from draining of experience; provides light</td><td>30,000</td><td>70</td><td>8</td><td>(2)</td></tr><tr><td>the Magi</td><td>Sustains and gives a bonus of +1+MB(3) to intelligence; gives a bonus of +1d5+MB(5) to AC; gives a bonus of +1+MB(3) to searching; gives resistance to confusion; protects from draining of experience; enables the wearer to see all invisible creatures</td><td>30,000</td><td>70</td><td>8</td><td>(1), (2)</td></tr><tr><td>Trickery</td><td>Sustains dexterity; gives a bonus of +1+MB(3) to dexterity, speed, searching, stealth and infravision (10 feet per +1); gives resistance to poison and nexus</td><td>30,000</td><td>70</td><td>8</td><td>(2)</td></tr><tr><td>Weaponmastery</td><td>Sustains and gives a bonus of 1+MB(2) to strength, and sustains constitution; gives a bonus of 1+MB(4) to to-hit and damage, calculated independently for each; gives resistance to fear and disenchantment; protects from draining of experience</td><td>30,000</td><td>70</td><td>8</td><td>(2)</td></tr></table><p>Notes:<ol type="1"><li>Has a chance to be cursed, in which case the bonus becomes a penalty (i.e. positive becomes negative) and the sale value becomes 0<li>For an explanation of the MB(x) notation, see a further page (TBD)</ol><ul><li>All amulets weigh 0.3 lbs<li>All amulets cannot be harmed by acid, cold, fire or lightning</ul></div></div>

